<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-05T06:00:00-05:00" n="215" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d215">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                        </head>
                        <p>On August 24, 1954, during a period of political crisis in Brazil,
                            President <persName corresp="#p_VGD1">Vargas</persName> committed
                            suicide, and Vice President <persName corresp="#p_CFJ1">João Café
                                Filho</persName> succeeded to the Presidency. Documentation
                            concerning these events and the United States reaction is in files
                            732.00 and 732.11 for 1954.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>